<HEADLINE> Bears Resume Talks With McNown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- The Chicago Bears and holdout rookie quarterback  
Cade McNown resumed contract talks Sunday, with the two sides 
exchanging proposals. 
</P>
<P>
	McNown and his agent, Tom Condon, will fly to Chicago on Monday  
to meet with Bears negotiator Jim Miller, the team said in a news 
release. 
</P>
<P>
	``The status of the negotiations has not changed, we'll just  
continue our discussions in person,'' Miller said. 
</P>
<P>
	There are concerns that unless the former UCLA star gets to  
training camp soon, he will be too far behind to learn the Bears' 
new offensive system and won't be able to start the season opener. 
</P>
