<HEADLINE> Joe Who Wins Eddie Read Handicap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) -- Joe Who won his third straight Del Mar  
turf race Sunday, taking the lead in the final strides to capture 
the $400,000 Eddie Read Handicap by a neck over Ladies Din. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Chris Antley and carrying 116 pounds, Joe Who covered  
1 1/8 miles in 1:48 3-5 and paid $15.40, $6.20 and $4.80. 
</P>
<P>
	The win was the 14th in 31 lifetime starts for Joe Who and was  
worth $240,000. The 6-year-old Brazilian-bred son of Jolly Quick 
won twice on the grass at Del Mar last summer. 
</P>
<P>
	Ladies Din, ridden by Kent Desormeaux and carrying 119 pounds,  
finished a half-length in front of Bouccaneer and returned $4.20 
and $3.40. 
</P>
<P>
	Bouccaneer, a 30-1 longshot, paid $9.80 to show.  
  	   	
</P>
