<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Saturday's Baseball Trades </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	A look at the deals made Saturday before baseball's non-waiver  
trade deadline of midnight EDT: 
</P>
<P>
	-- Kansas City Royals traded RHP Kevin Appier (9-9, 4.87 ERA) to  
the Oakland Athletics for RHP Blake Stein (0-0, 16.88), RHP Brad 
Rigby (3-4, 4.33) and minor league RHP Jeff D'Amico. 
</P>
<P>
	-- Oakland Athletics traded RHP Billy Taylor (1-5, 26 saves,  
3.98) to the New York Mets for RHPs Jason Isringhausen (1-3, 1 
save, 6.41) and Greg McMichael (1-1, 4.82). 
</P>
<P>
	-- New York Mets traded OF Brian McRae (.221, 8 HRs, 36 RBIs),  
LHP Rigo Beltran (1-1, 3.48) and minor league OF Thomas Johnson to 
the Colorado Rockies for OF Darryl Hamilton (.303, 4, 24) and LHP 
Chuck McElroy (3-1, 6.20). 
</P>
<P>
	-- St. Louis Cardinals traded INF Shawon Dunston (.307, 5, 25) to  
the New York Mets for minor league INF Craig Paquette. 
</P>
<P>
	-- Chicago Cubs traded LHP Terry Mulholland (6-6, 5.15) and INF  
Jose Hernandez (.272, 15, 43) to the Atlanta Braves for minor 
league LHP Micah Bowie, minor league RHP Ruben Quevedo and a minor 
league player to be named. 
</P>
<P>
	-- San Diego Padres traded utilityman Jim Leyritz (.239, 8, 21)  
to the New York Yankees for minor league RHP Geraldo Padua. 
</P>
<P>
	-- Baltimore Orioles traded pitcher Juan Guzman (5-9, 4.18) and  
cash to the Cincinnati Reds for minor league pitchers B.J. Ryan and 
Jacobo Sequea. 
</P>
<P>
	-- Detroit Tigers traded RHP Bryce Florie (2-1, 4.56) to the  
Boston Red Sox for minor league LHP Mike Maroth. 
</P>
<P>
	-- Florida Marlins traded minor league RHP Brandon Villafuerte to  
the Detroit Tigers for minor league RHP Mike Drumright. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
