<DOCNO> APW19990801.0024 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-01 18:26:52 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Favre Joins Packers' Camp </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- Brett Favre may have looked a little  
rusty in his 1999 training camp debut, but his presence was 
welcomed. 
</P>
<P>
	Favre, who missed the first days of camp while in Mississippi  
with his wife and their baby, arrived Saturday and went through a 
Sunday morning workout of more than two hours with his teammates. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was good to have Brett Favre back here,'' coach Ray Rhodes  
said. ``Brett brings a lot of spark to our offensive unit and 
that's big for our football team.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Favre's second daughter, Breleigh Ann, was born five weeks  
premature July 13 in Hattiesburg, Miss., and was in a hospital 
until Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Quarterbacks Rick Mirer, Matt Hasselbeck, Aaron Brooks and  
Ronnie McAda picked up the slack for the three-time MVP while he 
was gone. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's a little rusty but we love to have him back,'' offensive  
coordinator Sherm Lewis said. ``It looks great to have him in there 
and I think the guys feel good when he's there. I think he was a 
little rusty throwing the ball, but that's it.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
