</P>
<P>
	MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Rondell White hit a three-run homer and scored  
twice during Montreal's nine-run fourth inning as the Expos beat 
the bumbling Milwaukee Brewers 10-4 today. All nine Montreal runs 
in the fourth were unearned as Milwaukee put on a comical display 
of poor fielding and throwing. The Brewers, who made five errors in 
the game, made three in the fourth inning. 

</P>
