<HEADLINE> Two Earthquakes Shake Aleutians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PALMER, Alaska (AP) -- Two earthquakes shook the Aleutian Islands  
Sunday, but there were no reports of damage or injuries. 
</P>
<P>
	The first, a moderate 5.5 quake, jolted Adak at 4:48 a.m. The  
quake was centered about 30 miles southeast of Adak, about halfway 
down the island chain, and was felt strongly on the island, said 
Guy Urban of the Alaska Tsunami Warning Center. 
</P>
<P>
	The second was a magnitude 4.9 quake, which shook Atka at 12:11  
p.m. It was centered about 60 miles southeast of Atka. 
  	   	
</P>
