	Cohen Meets Georgian President  
</P>
<P>
	TBILISI, Georgia (AP) -- Defense Secretary William Cohen promised  
Georgia's president today that the United States would continue to 
help the Caucasus nation develop its armed forces. Cohen met for an 
hour with President Eduard Shevardnadze and Georgian Defense 
Minister David Tevzadze on the last day of a tour that included 
Japan, South Korea and Ukraine. Cohen said that Georgia had become 
a model of a democratic state, and for that reason the United 
States would keep up its aid to the Georgian military. 

</P>
