league-leading total to 40 as the Chicago Cubs beat the New York 
Mets 17-10 yesterday. It's the third time Sosa has reached 40 
homers in a season. He has three multihomer games this year and 36 
for his career. Dan Serafini (3-2) picked up the win with one 
inning of scoreless relief. Jason Isringhausen (1-3) took the loss, 
giving up five runs on five hits and three walks in three-plus 
innings. The Cubs scored a season-high seven runs in the first. 

</P>
