	McGwire Hits 496th Run  
</P>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Mark McGwire hit his 496th career home run and  
J.D. Drew broke a sixth-inning tie with a solo shot as the St. 
Louis Cardinals beat the Colorado Rockies 6-5 last night. McGwire 
has 12 homers in his last 16 games and 39 overall, one behind major 
league leader Sammy Sosa of the Chicago Cubs. McGwire tied his own 
record of 219 homers in four consecutive seasons. He also did it 
from 1995-98. Cardinals starter Larry Luebbers lasted 5 2-3 innings 
and gave up four runs on eight hits. 

</P>
