<HEADLINE> Ripken Scratched From Orioles Lineup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEATTLE (AP) -- Cal Ripken, one homer away from 400 in his  
career, was scratched from the Baltimore Orioles' lineup against 
Seattle on Sunday because of stiffness in his back. 
</P>
<P>
	Ripken's status is day to day. Ripken, 32 hits short of 3,000,  
played in the first two games of the Mariners' series. 
</P>
<P>
	He went on the 15-day disabled list for the first time in his  
career April 20 with nerve irritation in his lower back. He was 
activated May 13. 
</P>
<P>
	He missed five games July 16-20 with a deep bone bruise in his  
right wrist that he suffered when he was hit by a pitch in a game 
against Montreal July 15. 
</P>
<P>
	Ripken is hitting .335 in 69 games this season with 15 home runs  
and 47 RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
	He will celebrate his 39th birthday Aug. 24.  
  	   	
</P>
