<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Signs of Possible Violence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Companies must be alert for all threatening incidents, not just  
by problem employees, violence prevention researchers note. 
Nevertheless, some types of people are more likely to turn violent. 
According to author Lynne McClure, here are traits to look for: 
</P>
<P>
	-- Keeping away from others.  
</P>
<P>
	-- Failure to take responsibility for their actions.  
</P>
<P>
	-- Rigid and controlling behavior.  
</P>
<P>
	-- Acting out anger, or seeing only their own point of view.  
</P>
<P>
	-- Talking one way and acting another.  
</P>
<P>
	-- Addictive behavior, used to escape reality.  
</P>
<P>
	-- Actions out of character, done to shock others.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
