<HEADLINE> Victory Gallop Wins Whitney Handicap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SARATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. (AP) -- Victory Gallop outdueled Behrens  
by a nose Sunday to win the 72nd running of the $600,000, Grade I 
Whitney Handicap at Saratoga. 
</P>
<P>
	It was 12 lengths back to the third-place finisher, Catienus, as  
Victory Gallop and Behrens dominated the field. 
</P>
<P>
	The order of finish was completed by Sir Bear, Testafly, Nite  
Dreamer, Social Charter and Connecting Terms. 
</P>
<P>
	Jerry Bailey rode his second Whitney winner in the last three  
years. He also guided Will's Way to victory in 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	For Behrens, it was another heart-breaking loss at Saratoga. Two  
years ago, he was edged by Deputy Commander in the Travers. 
</P>
<P>
	Victory Gallop trailed the field through the first six furlongs,  
allowing the early speedsters Social Charter, Testafly and Nite 
Dreamer to set the pace. Connecting Terms, Victory Gallop's 
entrymate who was supposed to be part of the early scenario, never 
got closer than fourth. 
</P>
<P>
	Midway on the far turn, Victory Gallop accelerated rapidly to  
join the leaders. By the time Victory Gallop entered the stretch, 
Behrens had rallied wide as well and had gained the lead. 
</P>
<P>
	Passing the eighth-pole, the two were on even terms, with  
Victory Gallop enjoying momentum that seemed likely to carry him 
past Behrens to a decisive victory. But Behrens dug in and the two 
battled evenly in the final yards with Victory Gallop emerging the 
winner by the narrowest of margins. 
</P>
<P>
	Victory Gallop carried co-highweight of 123 and Bailey 1 1/8 miles  
in 1:48.66 on the fast track to earn $360,000 for Prestonwood Farm 
with his third win in four starts this year. The colt by 
Cryptoclearance for the Mr. Prospector mare, Victorious Lil, now 
boasts career earnings of $3,505,895.00. The winning entry returned 
$3.80, $2.30 and $2.10. 
</P>
<P>
	Behrens paid $2.40 and $2.10, and Catienus was $2.10 to show.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
