<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Mexico 1, U.S. 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MEXICO CITY (AP) -- The goalkeeping of Kasey Keller could carry  
the United States only so far. 
</P>
<P>
	Mexico defeated the United States 1-0 on goal by Cuauahtemoc  
Blanco in sudden-death overtime Sunday to advance to the final of 
the Confederations Cup. 
</P>
<P>
	The Mexicans will play Brazil on Wednesday for the title. The  
United States will face Saudi Arabia for third place on Tuesday in 
Guadalajara. 
</P>
<P>
	Brazil routed Saudi Arabia 8-2 in the other semifinal in  
Guadalajara, with Ronaldinho scoring three times and Alex twice. 
</P>
<P>
	The United States, before a crowd of 80,000 at Azteca Stadium,  
was trying to pull off another stunner following its quarterfinal 
victory over Germany. 
</P>
<P>
	This would have been the Americans' first victory at Azteca  
Stadium. But the altitude of 7,350 feet and less than two days of 
rest were too much to overcome. 
</P>
<P>
	There was also the persistent Mexican attack, which left the  
U.S. team under siege and surviving thanks to Keller's exceptional 
work. 
</P>
<P>
	Blanco had been tied up by Jeff Agoos and later Eddie Lewis for  
most of the game. But five minutes into overtime he finally broke 
through. 
</P>
<P>
	He first tried to kick the loose ball with his right foot, but  
it bounced off a defender as Keller went to his left. Blanco then 
pushed the ball in the net for his fifth goal of the tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	The loss dropped the Americans' record to 6-3-1 this season.  
They are 0-16-1 at Azteca. 
</P>
<P>
	During regulation play, Mexico's first chance came in the second  
minute. Blanco sent a pass to Isaac Terrazas down the right side, 
but Terrazas' low shot was stopped by Keller. 
</P>
<P>
	Mexico relied on speed, featuring an attack down the right side  
with Terrazas, Jose Manuel Abundis up front and Blanco and Ramon 
Ramirez orchestrating play. 
</P>
<P>
	In the eighth minute, Keller dived to deflect a shot by Rafael  
Marquez. Two minutes later, he again went to his left to stop a 
shot by Ramirez that was heading for the upper corner. 
</P>
<P>
	Cobi Jones and Frankie Hejduk missed with wide shots during the  
same stretch, but the U.S. attackers never posed a serious threat 
to Mexican goalie Jorge Campos. 
</P>
<P>
	Keller saved the United States again in the 47th minute when he  
deflected a shot from a few yards away by Gerardo Torrado as the 
Mexicans kept the pressure on. 
</P>
<P>
	In the 53rd minute, Jones got away down the left side. He passed  
to Ernie Stewart whose clear shot was stopped by Campos. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones took advantage of a Mexican mistake in the 66th minute and  
swept down the left side. But his lob over the goalie went high 
over the crossbar. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
