<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Amato Wins Northwest Nationals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KENT, Wash. (AP) -- Joe Amato won his second straight NHRA  
national event Sunday at the 12th annual Prolong Super Lubricants 
Northwest Nationals. 
</P>
<P>
	Amato, the defending event champion in Top Fuel, sped down the  
track in 4.704 seconds at 306.95 mph, enough to hold off Doug 
Kalitta, who ran a 4.697 at 307.58. 
</P>
<P>
	It was Amato's fourth win this year and the second straight race  
where he defeated Kalitta in the final round. 
</P>
<P>
	Del Worsham earned his first victory in eight years when he  
raced his Pontiac Firebird to a 5.283 at 279.67 as Whit Bazemore 
lost traction and finished with a 7.302 at 163.67. 
</P>
<P>
	Kurt Johnson captured his third victory of the season when he  
covered the quarter-mile in 6.923 at 200.44 in his Chevrolet 
Camaro, edging out Jim Yates, who ran a 6.962 at 198.00. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
